        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 3:24AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 323 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Tontitown, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and dime to penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Wesley...                         Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...
Beaver Lake...                    Elkins...
Savoy...                          Tontitown...
Forum...                          Aurora...
Larue...                          Pea Ridge...
Cave Springs...                   Hobbs State Park...
Best...                           Clifty...
Georgetown...                     Withrow Springs State Park...
War Eagle...                      Highfill...
Vaughn...                         Monte Ne...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 50 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northwestern
Arkansas.</instruction>
